verses.roman:
jagāi mādhāi haite muñi se pāpiṣṭha
purīṣera kīṭa haite muñi se laghiṣṭha

synonyms: jagāi mādhāi—the two brothers Jagāi and Mādhāi; haite—than; muñi—I; se—that; pāpiṣṭha—more sinful; purīṣera—in stool; kīṭa—the worms; haite—than; muñi—I am; se—that; laghiṣṭha—lower.
translation: I am more sinful than Jagāi and Mādhāi and even lower than the worms in the stool.
